<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Mom&apos;s Computer SMS Consent Flow</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
        background: #f6f8fb;
        color: #0b1220;
      }

      .wrap {
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 32px 20px 60px;
      }

      .hero,
      .section {
        background: #ffffff;
        border: 1px solid #d7dee8;
        border-radius: 24px;
        padding: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(16, 24, 40, 0.06);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0 0 12px 0;
        font-size: 34px;
        line-height: 1.1;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0 0 12px 0;
        font-size: 24px;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin: 0 0 14px 0;
      }

      .note {
        background: #f3f7ff;
        border: 1px solid #d6e6ff;
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 16px 18px;
        margin-top: 18px;
      }

      .legal-links {
        margin-top: 14px;
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .legal-links a {
        display: inline-block;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: #ffffff;
        background: #1e73e8;
        padding: 10px 14px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .steps {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 22px;
      }

      .steps li {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      .gallery {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
        gap: 18px;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      .shot {
        background: #f8fafc;
        border: 1px solid #d7dee8;
        border-radius: 20px;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .shot img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
      }

      .caption {
        padding: 12px 14px 16px;
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: #475467;
      }

      .footer-note {
        margin-top: 12px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #667085;
      }

      a.inline-link {
        color: #1e73e8;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .wrap {
          padding: 18px 12px 40px;
        }

        .hero,
        .section {
          padding: 18px;
          border-radius: 18px;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: 28px;
        }

        h2 {
          font-size: 22px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="hero">
        <h1>Mom&apos;s Computer SMS Consent Flow</h1>
        <p>
          This page documents the in-app SMS consent and phone verification flow used by Mom&apos;s Computer.
          Users enter their mobile phone number during signup and receive a one-time 6-digit verification
          code before account creation is completed.
        </p>
        <p>
          The signup screen includes links to the Privacy Policy and Terms &amp; Conditions, plus
          SMS disclosure language stating that transactional messages may be sent for account
          verification and support.
        </p>

        <div class="note">
          <p><strong>Program type:</strong> Transactional / account verification / support-related SMS</p>
          <p><strong>Message frequency:</strong> Varies based on user activity</p>
          <p><strong>Opt-out:</strong> Reply STOP to opt out</p>
          <p><strong>Help:</strong> Reply HELP for help</p>
          <p><strong>Rates:</strong> Message and data rates may apply</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-links">
          <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>
          <a href="/terms-and-conditions">Terms &amp; Conditions</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>How users opt in</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li>User opens the Mom&apos;s Computer signup screen and begins account creation.</li>
          <li>User enters first name, last name, email address, phone number, and password.</li>
          <li>User taps <strong>Send Code</strong> to request a one-time verification text message.</li>
          <li>User receives the SMS code and enters it into the app to verify the phone number.</li>
          <li>User sees legal links and SMS disclosure language on the signup screen before finishing account creation.</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="footer-note">
          Privacy Policy:
          <a class="inline-link" href="/privacy-policy">/privacy-policy</a><br />
          Terms &amp; Conditions:
          <a class="inline-link" href="/terms-and-conditions">/terms-and-conditions</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Signup flow screenshots</h2>

        <div class="gallery">
          <div class="shot">
            <img src="/sms-consent/screen-1-signup-top.png" alt="Signup context screen" />
            <div class="caption">
              Signup context showing the account creation form and the phone number section within the normal signup flow.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="shot">
            <img src="/sms-consent/screen-3-send-code.png" alt="Send code step" />
            <div class="caption">
              User enters a mobile phone number and taps <strong>Send Code</strong> to request a one-time verification SMS.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="shot">
            <img src="/sms-consent/screen-2-phone-code.png" alt="Verify code step" />
            <div class="caption">
              User enters the 6-digit verification code received by text message to verify the phone number.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="shot">
            <img src="/sms-consent/screen-4-legal-copy.png" alt="Legal disclosure" />
            <div class="caption">
              Signup screen showing the <strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong>, <strong>Privacy Policy</strong>, and SMS disclosure language for transactional messages.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>